{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a6e417cc3fb48d67e97", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9a"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "62c481f101514d218a7934dc", "title": "JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 2)", "isVisible": true}], "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "approximateTimeRequired": 120, "question": {"text": "Two point charges <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi></math>&nbsp;each are placed at a distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math> apart. A third point charge <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math> is placed at a distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> from mid-point on the perpendicular bisector. The value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;at which charge <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math> will experience the maximum Coulomb&#39;s force is:", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "vSxP8", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "MvECU", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "uESDd", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>d</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "mlBUE", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/25284b10-22d6-400c-9e5e-424dbd9ad6ad-image.png\" style=\"width: 230px; height: 240px;\" /></p><p>The distance between&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math>.</p><p>The force between&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi></math>&nbsp;will be&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>q</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>.</p><p>From the given figure we can see that only vertical components of the forces will add, and the&nbsp;horizontal components will get cancelled out.&nbsp;Therefore,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mi>q</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mi>q</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mi>r</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>q</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></msup></mfrac></math></p><p>For force to be maximum,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>q</mi><mi>Q</mi><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><msup><mfenced><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "questionLabels": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ53339496", "source": "EM", "bucket": "Must Do Ques (JEE Main) - Any Difficulty", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "category": null, "microConcepts": [], "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubj